According to the United States Census Bureau,

'Median home values adjusted for inflation nearly quadrupled over the 60-year period since the first housing census in 1940. 
The median value of single-family homes in the United States rose from $30,600 in 1940 to $119,600 in 2000, after adjusting for inflation (see graph).'

https://www.census.gov/data/tables/time-series/dec/coh-values.html
